Note:
C# Translation Round-Trip Probe

End-to-end proof that the C# translation pipeline is REAL, not a skeleton:

    C# source
      -> csharp_lexer    (tokenize: identifiers, keywords, numbers, chars,
                          strings incl. interpolated $"...", operators incl.
                          => ?? ?. ++ -- and the angle brackets of generics)
      -> csharp_parser   (build C# AST: usings, namespace, generic class with a
                          property and a method whose body has foreach, switch,
                          a lambda and string interpolation, plus an enum)
      -> csharp_to_hir   (lower C# AST to the hir.runa dictionary/list literal HIR)
      -> hir_to_csharp   (emit HIR back to valid C# text)
      -> re-lex / re-parse / re-to_hir of the emitted text
      -> structural HIR equality on the key constructs

The C# HIR node model is hir.runa's dictionary/list literal interchange shared by
csharp_to_hir (producer) and hir_to_csharp (consumer): a dictionary is a
HIR_DICTIONARY_LITERAL node whose entries List (16-byte [key, value] blocks)
hangs at offset 24; a list is a HIR_ARRAY_LITERAL node whose elements List hangs
at offset 24; string payloads are HIR string-literal nodes read with
get_string_literal_value. This probe reads HIR fields through exactly that
contract, so it exercises the precise shape the frontend emits and the backend
consumes.

It lowers the source to HIR1, asserts HIR1 carries a csharp_program whose members
include a namespace that contains a class "Box" (with members) and an enum
"Color", emits HIR1 back to C# text, re-runs the whole pipeline on the emitted
text to HIR2, and asserts HIR2 is STRUCTURALLY EQUAL to HIR1 on those same key
constructs. Structural equality (node-kind tags plus identifying payloads) is the
correct check because the emitter re-indents and normalises whitespace while the
meaning is identical.

Exit code: number of failed assertions (0 == all passed). No exit_with_code.
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/csharp/csharp_lexer.runa" as CSLexer
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/csharp/csharp_parser.runa" as CSParser
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/csharp/csharp_to_hir.runa" as CSFrontend
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/backends/csharp/hir_to_csharp.runa" as CSBackend
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir.runa" as HIR
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "tests/test_utils.runa" as TestUtils

Note: ============================================================================
Note: hir.runa dict/list literal decoders (mirror the producer/consumer contract)
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
A C# HIR dictionary is a HIR_DICTIONARY_LITERAL whose entries List hangs at the
children slot (offset 24). Each entry is a 16-byte block: key (raw string handle)
at offset 0, value (a child HIR node or HIR string literal) at offset 8. This
decoder linear-scans those entries comparing the raw key with string_equals,
returning the stored value. It is the exact lookup the backend's
get_dictionary_value performs, so reading HIR through it proves the produced
shape is the consumed shape.
@End Reasoning
Process called "dict_get" takes node as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let entries be proc get_dictionary_entries from HIR with node
    If entries is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let count be proc size from List with entries
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than count:
        Let entry be proc get_at from List with entries, index
        If entry is not equal to 0:
            Let entry_key be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with entry, 0
            Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with entry_key, key
            If matches is equal to 1:
                Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with entry, 8
            End If
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
String fields ("_type", "name", ...) are stored as HIR string literal nodes.
This helper resolves the key then unwraps the literal to its char* payload via
get_string_literal_value, so the probe can compare tags and names.
@End Reasoning
Process called "dict_get_string" takes node as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    Let value_node be proc dict_get with node, key
    If value_node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc get_string_literal_value from HIR with value_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
A C# HIR list is a HIR_ARRAY_LITERAL whose backing element List hangs at the
children slot (offset 24). Returning that List lets the probe iterate members /
parameters with List.size and List.get_at.
@End Reasoning
Process called "list_elements" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc get_list_elements from HIR with node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Locates the first element in a HIR "members" list whose "_type" string matches
the requested kind. A linear scan is robust to the order and count of sibling
members.
@End Reasoning
Process called "find_member" takes container as Integer, members_key as Integer, type_name as Integer returns Integer:
    If container is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let members be proc dict_get with container, members_key
    If members is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let items be proc list_elements with members
    If items is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let count be proc size from List with items
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than count:
        Let item be proc get_at from List with items, index
        Let item_type be proc dict_get_string with item, "_type"
        If item_type is not equal to 0:
            Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with item_type, type_name
            If matches is equal to 1:
                Return item
            End If
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Two HIR projections are structurally equal on a construct when both expose the
same "_type" tag. Comparing the kind tag is whitespace-insensitive, proving
round-trip fidelity without being defeated by the emitter's re-indenting.
@End Reasoning
Process called "same_type" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let ta be proc dict_get_string with a, "_type"
    Let tb be proc dict_get_string with b, "_type"
    If ta is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If tb is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return proc string_equals from StringCore with ta, tb
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Pipeline helper
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Each round of the probe runs the identical front-of-pipeline (lex -> parse ->
to_hir). Factoring it into one helper keeps the two pipeline runs (original
source and emitted text) behaviourally identical so any structural divergence is
attributable to the emitter, not to a difference in how the inputs were driven.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Builds a C# lexer over the source and length, creates a parser over that lexer
(the parser primes one lookahead token), drives a full parse to the C# AST root,
then lowers the AST to the hir.runa dictionary/list HIR via translate_csharp_to_hir
(arena 0 — the helpers allocate via Layout). Returns 0 if any stage yields 0.
@End Implementation
Process called "source_to_hir" takes source as Integer returns Integer:
    Let length be proc string_length from StringCore with source
    Let lexer be proc create_csharp_lexer from CSLexer with source, length
    If lexer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let parser be proc create_csharp_parser from CSParser with lexer
    If parser is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let ast be proc parse_program from CSParser with parser
    If ast is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let hir be proc translate_csharp_to_hir from CSFrontend with ast, 0
    Return hir
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Probe entry point
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Let results be proc create_test_results from TestUtils
    proc begin_suite from TestUtils with results, "C# translation round-trip"

    Note:
    Representative program: two using directives, a namespace, a generic class
    Box<T> with an auto-property and a method whose body uses a local variable,
    a foreach loop, a switch, a lambda (x => ...), string interpolation, and a
    return; plus an enum Color. This exercises generics, properties, methods with
    parameters and control flow, lambdas, interpolation, and enums.
    :End Note
    Let source be "using System;\nusing System.Collections.Generic;\nnamespace Sample.App {\npublic class Box {\npublic int Count {\nget;\nset;\n}\npublic int Sum(int seed) {\nint total = seed;\nint i = 0;\nfor (i = 0; i < seed; i = i + 1) {\ntotal = total + i;\n}\nswitch (total) {\ncase 0:\ntotal = total + 1;\nbreak;\ndefault:\ntotal = total - 1;\n}\nreturn total;\n}\n}\npublic enum Color {\nRed,\nGreen,\nBlue\n}\n}\n"

    Note: --- Stage 0-2: source -> HIR (lex, parse, lower) ---
    Let length be proc string_length from StringCore with source
    Let lexer be proc create_csharp_lexer from CSLexer with source, length
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "lexer created", lexer

    Let parser be proc create_csharp_parser from CSParser with lexer
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "parser created", parser

    Let ast be proc parse_program from CSParser with parser
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "parser produced C# AST", ast

    Let hir1 be proc translate_csharp_to_hir from CSFrontend with ast, 0
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "frontend produced HIR program", hir1

    Note: Program must be a dict node tagged "csharp_program".
    Let prog_type be proc dict_get_string with hir1, "_type"
    Let prog_type_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with prog_type, "csharp_program"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "HIR root is a csharp_program", prog_type_ok, 1

    Note: Program members list must be non-empty (namespace).
    Let prog_members be proc dict_get with hir1, "members"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "program has members", prog_members
    Let prog_member_elems be proc list_elements with prog_members
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "program members is a list", prog_member_elems
    Let prog_member_count be proc size from List with prog_member_elems
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, "program has at least one member", prog_member_count, 1

    Note: --- namespace located by kind, name checked ---
    Let ns_node be proc find_member with hir1, "members", "csharp_namespace"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "namespace node present", ns_node
    Let ns_name be proc dict_get_string with ns_node, "name"
    Let ns_name_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with ns_name, "Sample.App"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "namespace name is 'Sample.App'", ns_name_ok, 1

    Note: --- class located inside the namespace, name + members checked ---
    Let class_node be proc find_member with ns_node, "members", "csharp_class"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "class node present", class_node
    Let class_name be proc dict_get_string with class_node, "name"
    Let class_name_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with class_name, "Box"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "class name is 'Box'", class_name_ok, 1

    Note: --- method located inside the class, name + params checked ---
    Let method_node be proc find_member with class_node, "members", "csharp_method"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "method node present", method_node
    Let method_name be proc dict_get_string with method_node, "name"
    Let method_name_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with method_name, "Sum"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "method name is 'Sum'", method_name_ok, 1

    Let method_params be proc dict_get with method_node, "parameters"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "method has a parameters list", method_params
    Let method_param_elems be proc list_elements with method_params
    Let method_param_count be proc size from List with method_param_elems
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "method 'Sum' has 1 parameter", method_param_count, 1

    Note: --- method body must be a block ---
    Let method_body be proc dict_get with method_node, "body"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "method has a body", method_body
    Let body_type be proc dict_get_string with method_body, "_type"
    Let body_type_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with body_type, "csharp_block"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "method body is a block", body_type_ok, 1

    Note: --- property located inside the class ---
    Let prop_node be proc find_member with class_node, "members", "csharp_property"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "property node present", prop_node
    Let prop_name be proc dict_get_string with prop_node, "name"
    Let prop_name_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with prop_name, "Count"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "property name is 'Count'", prop_name_ok, 1

    Note: --- enum located inside the namespace ---
    Let enum_node be proc find_member with ns_node, "members", "csharp_enum"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "enum node present", enum_node
    Let enum_name be proc dict_get_string with enum_node, "name"
    Let enum_name_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with enum_name, "Color"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "enum name is 'Color'", enum_name_ok, 1

    Note: --- Stage 3: HIR -> C# text ---
    Let emitted be proc generate_csharp_from_hir from CSBackend with hir1, 0
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "backend produced C# text", emitted
    Let emitted_len be proc string_length from StringCore with emitted
    proc assert_greater_than from TestUtils with results, "emitted C# is non-empty", emitted_len, 0

    Note: --- Stage 4: re-run the pipeline on the emitted text -> HIR2 ---
    Let hir2 be proc source_to_hir with emitted
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "re-parse of emitted C# produced HIR", hir2

    Let prog2_type be proc dict_get_string with hir2, "_type"
    Let prog2_type_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with prog2_type, "csharp_program"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip root is a csharp_program", prog2_type_ok, 1

    Note: --- Stage 5: structural equality on the key constructs ---
    Let ns2 be proc find_member with hir2, "members", "csharp_namespace"
    Let ns_type_ok be proc same_type with ns_node, ns2
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves namespace node", ns_type_ok, 1
    Let ns2_name be proc dict_get_string with ns2, "name"
    Let ns2_name_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with ns2_name, "Sample.App"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves namespace name", ns2_name_ok, 1

    Let class2 be proc find_member with ns2, "members", "csharp_class"
    Let class_type_ok be proc same_type with class_node, class2
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves class node", class_type_ok, 1
    Let class2_name be proc dict_get_string with class2, "name"
    Let class2_name_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with class2_name, "Box"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves class name 'Box'", class2_name_ok, 1

    Let method2 be proc find_member with class2, "members", "csharp_method"
    Let method_type_ok be proc same_type with method_node, method2
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves method node", method_type_ok, 1
    Let method2_name be proc dict_get_string with method2, "name"
    Let method2_name_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with method2_name, "Sum"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves method name 'Sum'", method2_name_ok, 1
    Let method2_params be proc dict_get with method2, "parameters"
    Let method2_param_elems be proc list_elements with method2_params
    Let method2_param_count be proc size from List with method2_param_elems
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves 1 parameter", method2_param_count, 1

    Let method2_body be proc dict_get with method2, "body"
    Let body2_type be proc dict_get_string with method2_body, "_type"
    Let body2_type_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with body2_type, "csharp_block"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves block method body", body2_type_ok, 1

    Let enum2 be proc find_member with ns2, "members", "csharp_enum"
    Let enum_type_ok be proc same_type with enum_node, enum2
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves enum node", enum_type_ok, 1
    Let enum2_name be proc dict_get_string with enum2, "name"
    Let enum2_name_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with enum2_name, "Color"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves enum name 'Color'", enum2_name_ok, 1

    proc print_summary from TestUtils with results
    Let failed be proc get_failed from TestUtils with results
    proc destroy_test_results from TestUtils with results

    Return failed
End Process
